#: ../../enterprise_external_storage/windows-network-drive_configuration.rst:141
msgid "Windows Network Drive Listener"
msgstr ""

#: ../../enterprise_external_storage/windows-network-drive_configuration.rst:143
msgid ""
"The SMB protocol supports registering for notifications of file changes "
"on remote Windows SMB storage servers. Notifications are more efficient "
"than polling for changes, as polling requires scanning the whole SMB "
"storage. ownCloud supports SMB notifications with an ``occ`` command, "
"``occ wnd:listen``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../enterprise_external_storage/windows-network-drive_configuration.rst:145
msgid ""
"The notifier only works with remote storages on Windows servers. It does "
"not work reliably with Linux servers due to technical limitations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../enterprise_external_storage/windows-network-drive_configuration.rst:147
msgid ""
"Your ``smbclient`` versions needs to be 4.x, as older versions do not "
"support notifications."
msgstr ""

#: ../../enterprise_external_storage/windows-network-drive_configuration.rst:149
msgid ""
"The ownCloud server needs to know about changes of files on integrated "
"storages so that the changed files will be synced to the ownCloud server,"
" and to desktop sync clients. Files changed through the ownCloud Web "
"interface or sync clients are automatically updated in the ownCloud "
"filecache, but this is not possible when files are changed directly on "
"remote SMB storage mounts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../enterprise_external_storage/windows-network-drive_configuration.rst:151
msgid ""
"To create a new SMB notification, start a listener on your ownCloud "
"server with ``occ wnd:listen``. The listener marks changed files, and a "
"background job updates the file metadata."
msgstr ""

